<section class="section">
  <h2>Social Engineering & Awareness Testing</h2>
  <p>
    Technical defenses matter, but attackers still rely heavily on people.
    This engagement helps you understand how staff respond to realistic but controlled
    social engineering attempts, and how to build long-term awareness.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>What This Service Covers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Authorized phishing simulations tailored to your environment.</li>
      <li>Scenarios aligned with real-world attacker tactics, not scare tactics.</li>
      <li>Measurement of click rates, reporting rates, and response patterns.</li>
      <li>Optional follow-up education materials or debrief sessions.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>How the Engagement Works</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>We define clear boundaries, objectives, and communication plans.</li>
      <li>Campaigns are designed to be realistic but non-disruptive.</li>
      <li>Only authorized scenarios are used; no surprises for stakeholders.</li>
      <li>Results are anonymized where possible and used for improvement, not blame.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>What You Learn</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>How likely staff are to engage with suspicious messages.</li>
      <li>Which types of lures and pretexts are most effective.</li>
      <li>Where training, communication, or process updates are needed.</li>
      <li>Practical recommendations to strengthen your human defenses.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Is This Right for You?</h3>
    <p>
      Choose this service if you want to go beyond generic awareness training and
      measure how your organization responds to realistic, controlled scenarios.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:10px;">
      <a href="contact.html" class="hero-btn primary">Plan a Social Engineering Exercise</a>
    </p>
  </div>
